<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="a" from="2" to="5" step="1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="b" from="2" to="4" step="1" exclude="$a"/>
  <function name="f">$a*ln(x)</function>
  <number name="L3">$b*($$f($b) + $$f(2*$b) + $$f(3*$b))</number>
  <number name="R3">$b*($$f(2*$b) + $$f(3*$b) + $$f(4*$b))</number>  
</setup>

<p>
  This exercise asks you to develop the structure of <m>L_3</m> and <m>R_3</m>, the left and right Riemann sums with <m>3</m> subintervals, for <m>f(x) = $f</m> on the interval <m>[$b, <math simplify>4*$b</math>]</m>.
</p>   

<p>
  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
      <p>
        For the given information, fill in the following blanks to identify the values of <m>\Delta x</m> and <m>x_i</m> for <m>i = 0</m> to <m>i = 3</m>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>\Delta x = </m><answer>$b</answer>
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>x_0 = </m><answer>$b</answer>, <m>x_1 = </m><answer>2*$b</answer>, <m>x_2 = </m><answer>3*$b</answer>, <m>x_3 = </m><answer>4*$b</answer> 
      </p>
    </li>  
    <li>
      <p>
        Now use your work in (a) to state the general structure of <m>L_3</m> and <m>R_3</m> in terms of the function <m>f</m> by filling in the blanks below:
      </p>  
      <p>
        <m>L_3 = f(</m><answer>$b</answer><m>) \cdot </m><answer>$b</answer><m> + f(</m><answer>2*$b</answer><m>) \cdot </m><answer>$b</answer><m> + f(</m><answer>3*$b</answer><m>) \cdot </m><answer>$b</answer>  
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>R_3 = f(</m><answer>2*$b</answer><m>) \cdot </m><answer>$b</answer><m> + f(</m><answer>3*$b</answer><m>) \cdot </m><answer>$b</answer><m> + f(</m><answer>4*$b</answer><m>) \cdot </m><answer>$b</answer>  
      </p>      
    </li>  
    <li>
      <p>
        Finally, use the fact that <m>f(x) = $f</m> to update your Riemann sums using the rule for the function.  For example, if one of the terms in (b) was <q><m>f(3) \cdot 1.5</m></q>, below you'd now enter  <q><m>$$f(3) \cdot 1.5</m></q>.
      </p>  
      <p>
        <m>L_3 = </m><answer>$$f($b)</answer><m> \cdot </m><answer>$b</answer><m> + </m><answer>$$f(2*$b)</answer><m> \cdot </m><answer>$b</answer><m> + </m><answer>$$f(3*$b)</answer><m> \cdot </m><answer>$b</answer>  
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>R_3 = </m><answer>$$f(2*$b)</answer><m> \cdot </m><answer>$b</answer><m> + </m><answer>$$f(3*$b)</answer><m> \cdot </m><answer>$b</answer><m> \cdot </m><answer>$$f(4*$b)</answer><m> \cdot </m><answer>$b</answer>
      </p> 
    </li>   
    <li>
      <p>
        Finally, use a computational device to numerically evaluate the Riemann sums in (c) and report them to at least 2 decimal places of accuracy in the blanks below.
      </p>  
      <p>
        <m>L_3 = </m><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute>$L3</answer>
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>R_3 = </m><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute>$R3</answer>
      </p> 
    </li>  
  </ol>  
</p>  